## Portfolio optimisation. 

## Sharpe Ratio Calculation and Optimisation

I found this brilliant video on YouTube that I will follow along to achieve this objective.  

[Portfolio Optimization in Python: Boost Your Financial Performance - YouTube]
<iframe title="Portfolio Optimization in Python: Boost Your Financial Performance" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/9GA2WlYFeBU?feature=oembed" height="113" width="200" allowfullscreen="" allow="fullscreen" style="aspect-ratio: 1.76991 / 1; width: 100%; height: 100%;"></iframe>


Using the Scipy's minimise function, I can basically get the combination of weights that will maximise the sharpe ratio. These new weights can then be applied on the portfolio to get the optimum number of stocks one should hold to maintain said sharpe ratio. 

This is basically shown with the following equation. 

$$
new No. of Shares = (totalValueofPortfolio \times new Weights)\div Price Per share
$$
